    ISenseServiceCallback 
    SenseService
    Main Sense service class.

    Activities can bind to this service and call functions to: log in; register; start sensing; start/stop individual sensor modules; set and get properties; When the #toggleMain(boolean) method is called to start the sensing, the service starts itself and registers itself as a foreground service so it does not get easily killed by Android.
    SenseServiceStub
    Implementation of the service's AIDL interface.
    ServiceStateHelper
    This class is responsible for keeping track of the Sense service state and updating the status bar notification when the service is started or changes login status.
